{
  "stem": "3040.1",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Invited them, people who didn't have families.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "They would participate.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Of course, the children were all festively dressed.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And the table was decked with everything that we, we could muster, all silver.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Everything that we had in any place was on that table, at the seder, to show up the riches that we-- and then the connection, because the connection with the Exodus is such that when the Jews left Egypt, the ninth plague was complete darkness.",
      "word_count": 45
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And this is a time when the Jews took all the, the silver and the gold and the valuable from the Egyptians.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And they carried it out from Egypt.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "So on that account I think, we put everything on the table to show off.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, every holiday had a special meaning because OK, we are now on, on Pesach.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Then the next holiday to Pesach is Shavuot, which we just celebrated last week.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And this was a special holiday because this is remembering the giving of the Torah.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And this is celebrating the giving of the Torah and the other special, different traditions.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "The-- all the synagogues are decorated with, with greens on that holiday.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "It's not done here so much.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But still, in the Hasidic circles, like in Borough Park, you'll still find they take branches.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "They cut the branches, fresh branches, and bring it into the shul to decorate it.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "After this is-- comes Rosh Hashanah because then it's nothing between, just the summer.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And Rosh Hashanah is the new year, the Jewish new year.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Again, everything was-- the center of everything was the shul, and then the home when we came back.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "These two places alternated with one another.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
